{
  "texts": [
    "In the selected research, using multiple datasets to evaluate model performance was commonplace.",
    "This approach is highly beneficial as it enables the assessment of model generalizability, facilitates a more comprehensive evaluation, and establishes benchmarks for the field.",
    "Datasets with varying difficulty levels, IRs, and feature spaces can expose the strengths and limitations of models.",
    "Using multiple datasets mitigates the risk of models overfitting to one particular dataset, ensuring models are more readily applicable to new and unseen data.",
    "Data represents a fundamental aspect of CSL in the medical field, and comprehending the used data types is paramount."
  ]
}